Whether an acceptilatio in partem debiti was valid had been disputed in Gaius’ time, iii. 172. Justinian's statement of the law must be taken subject to the distinction drawn by Ulpian: ‘si id, quod in stipulationem deductum est, divisionem non recipiat, acceptilatio in partem nullius erit momenti, ut puta si servitus fuit praedii rustici vel urbani.
